        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=41521&amp;TOPIC_ID=5165&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Fearing+in+ME&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I have been over at ME for 3 to 4 days now and those Goranga guy's exp just flies like crazy.  Just go out of DP zone, hang a right and set up on that wall.  Just keep a distance from zone mind you.  Get 49 pet out, i pull with splurt, pet attack, fear, darkness, ignite blood, lich, and just repeat the fear and darkness, no need for other dots cos it waste too much mana.  Bascially, you want lesser dots also because you don't wanna get aggro and let the pet do most of the tanking, and try to have steelskin up and harmshield mem just incase people train you and you have to run for zone.  The things i have mem when doing this is Deflux, lich/BoD, Ignite blood, Splurt, dooming darkness, invoke fear, harmshield, feign death... I have both FD and HS mem is because there are too many trains and all the stuff around hits for at least 130+ so that means you are gonna die pretty quickly if you get more then one on you... I suggest not to attempt this until 54 because I was getting about 3 out of 10 resist from those guys.  Only pulll followers, gatherers, and lookouts any others that are around you shouldn't even think about.</P><P>Bartleby<BR>Always standing on the shoulders of giants...</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
